# CSS conventions

## Use nesting when possible

- Prefer **CSS nesting** instead of long selector chains.
- Nest selectors under the main scope (e.g. `section.form`, `section.gallery`).
- Use `&` for modifiers and pseudo-elements (e.g. `&.card`, `&::before`).

```css
/* Prefer: nested */
section.form {
  .flex-wrapper {
    display: flex;

    .content {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      
      .contact { ... }
    }
  }
}

/* Avoid: long flat chains */
section.form .flex-wrapper .content .contact { ... }
```

## Desktop first, then media queries

1. Write **desktop (default) styles first** in the main block.
2. Put **all mobile/tablet overrides** in `@media (max-width: ...)` at the **end** of the file or block.
3. Use **max-width** media queries for responsive overrides (mobile-first approach: base = small, then min-width for larger; or desktop-first: base = large, then max-width for smaller).

```css
section.example {
  /* 1. Desktop styles first */
  .flex-wrapper {
    display: flex;
    margin: -40px;
    > * { width: calc(50% - 80px); margin: 40px; }
  }

  /* 2. Media queries last (max-width = mobile/tablet overrides) */
  @media only screen and (max-width: 991px) {
    .flex-wrapper {
      display: block;
      margin: 0;
      > * { width: 100%; margin: 0 0 20px 0; }
    }
  }
}
```

## Summary

- Nest under a single root selector per component.
- Desktop layout first; no media query for the default.
- One or more `@media (max-width: ...)` blocks at the end for smaller viewports.
